[3.0.1]
* Fix broken image build: the LDAP dependency resolution stage was missing XWiki's "externals" Maven repository, so transitive deps of xwiki-platform-oldcore (css4j, css4j-dom4j, jodconverter-core) failed to resolve.

[3.0.0]
* Add LDAP single sign-on against the Cloudron user directory. Enables the Cloudron `ldap` addon, bakes the XWiki LDAP Authenticator extension into the image, and auto-configures xwiki.cfg from the CLOUDRON_LDAP_* variables on every boot. Cloudron users can log in with their Cloudron credentials; local accounts still work (trylocal). NOTE: the LDAP addon cannot be added to an existing install, so this requires a fresh install (no in-place upgrade from 2.x).

[2.0.0]
* Switch database from MySQL to PostgreSQL. This removes the manual one-time MySQL PROCESS-privilege grant and utf8mb4_bin collation step - XWiki now initializes with no manual database steps. NOTE: this is a database engine change, so it requires a fresh install (no in-place upgrade from 1.x).

[1.0.1]
* Document the required MySQL PROCESS privilege grant and utf8mb4_bin collation fix (post-install message + README).

[1.0.0]
* Initial release
